Just wandering around Mexico City

I think spending three days in Mexico City helped me prepare for the elevation. I feel good so far. Apparently the airport in Cusco was closed yesterday because of protesting so my timing seems good so far. I’m so excited I’ve been wanting to come here for a very long time. This is right up there with the pyramids in Egypt for me. 😃😃😃
Life at 12000 feet taking in the beauty and history of sacsayhuaman pronounced sexywoman. Peru is amazing #travel #peru #cusco #adventure #history #culture #sacsayhuaman #inca #preinca

Another day in Cusco and as it turns out most of the stuff I really wanted to see is unavailable because of protesters and their rocky road blocks so I’m going to head to the warmth of Lima a few days early and enjoy the comforts of city life and sea level. Last night heavy fireworks started around 2 am at least that’s when they woke me up it’s now 7 am and still going strong.  I’m kinda delirious and excited to knock out this last day and get outa here. Part of travel is not sweating the little stuff and finding the experience that’s available. When things don’t go your way it’s going to make a more interesting story anyway so bring it 😂 because we all love a good story #travel #cusco #peru #adventure #sightseeing

Welcome to magna-grecia today I took a little drive from Palermo to #selinunte and #segesta to see some 2500 year old Greek ruins. Imagine what it must have been like at its best.

These clouds are on a GOOOOOOD ONE !!! I did manage to get my morning walk and grocery run in right before it started storming again. It almost makes a person want to believe that the progeny of the titans are out there throwing thunder bolts and stirring up the sea. welcome to Syracuse second largest city of Ancient Greece. It has been attacked and or conquered by just about anyone who could muster a fleet of ships. It is located in the south east corner of what is now Sicily. It dates back to around 750 bc ish.

The ear of Dionysus “as seen in the new Indiana Jones movie” is supposed to have strange acoustic properties and is also alleged to have been a place of torture for prisoners of local ruling tyrant Dionysus him self. What appears to be certain is that this area was a quart for the gree temples of the time around 2500 years ago and for a few bucks you too can wander through them today at your leisure
